I have a story.
I have a hunting lodge right next to the city.
The nutria were climbing out of the river and causing damage to the crops, so I sat there.
When I arrived, I saw that there was a fisherman on the other side of the river.
I didn't want to make a mess, so I sat down quietly and the guy probably didn't notice me.
I hoped he would leave before something came out, but of course, the fox came out after a while.
I let her come within 40 meters before I decided to shoot.
The poor fisherman almost pissed himself, he was waving his headlamp all over the place, so I called out to him that it was a fox.
Before I got off the bench, I was livid.
In other words, a man's meadow can be a swamp.
On the other hand, it's not a war, it would have to be a series of coincidences for something to happen, you would probably be seen on a thermal imager, which almost everyone has today.
So, put it in a visible place, put the expensive things at your feet in your sleeping bag and you should be fine.
