The man from Hrob "shot" his girlfriend from Kostomlat
The man from Hrob inadvertently helped the officers to secure his nationwide wanted girlfriend from Kostomlaty, for whom an arrest warrant had been issued.
He himself called her.
He went about it in a roundabout way.
He first approached a passerby and made up a story that he had been robbed.
Officers were called to the scene and were left stunned when the alleged "victim" told them he had made the whole thing up in order to get the officers to come to the scene.
In fact, he just wanted to ask the police officers how to file a report with the Czech Police.
During the identity check of the man and his girlfriend, the officers found out that the woman is on the list of wanted persons, in a nationwide search, and an arrest warrant has been issued for her.
The case is therefore being dealt with by the Czech Police.
