The Bethlehem flame is in the Czech Republic, the scouts took it from Austria
Břeclav - The flame lit in Bethlehem, where according to Christian tradition Jesus Christ was born, is in the Czech Republic.
The scouts did not go to Vienna for him this time either due to the coronavirus pandemic. They took him from their Austrian colleagues in the morning at the Reintal - Břeclav border crossing.
They took it over at the border last year.
The Bethlehem Light is a beautiful Christmas tradition that we participate in every year with our group, and I look forward to it very much.
It is an honour for me to have been chosen, said scout Amálie Budíková to the journalists present.
While last year the handover took place at the Mikulov-Drasenhofen border crossing, directly on the border bridge, this year it took place at the Reintal-Břeclav border crossing in the car park.
However, the scouts usually travel by train to Vienna.
The distribution of the flame across the Czech Republic will not change.
The scouts traditionally set off with the Bethlehem light by train first to Brno, where they will hand it over to the diocesan bishop Vojtěch Cikrle.
On Saturday, 18 December, scout couriers will take care of the subsequent distribution of the light. They will travel by selected express trains and passenger trains.
From them, the light will be taken over by local scouts or volunteers at the stations, who will then continue to spread the flame throughout the Czech Republic, even to places where the tracks do not lead.
This year, too, the scouts must comply with the current measures to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.
It is going the same way as last year.
We recommend that both the delivery teams and the organisers of local events should of course wear masks, try to keep their distance, have as few people as possible, not sing to each other, in short, to behave in a way that is as safe as possible, described the spokesperson for the Bethlehem Light event, Zuzana Hrbková.
The tradition of the Bethlehem light, which travels through Europe, was born in 1986 in Austria.
The aim is to spread the idea of peace, friendship and peace along with the flame.
The Bethlehem light is a symbol of hope for believers, a light that overcomes the darkness.
In the Czech Republic, the scouts and guides have been taking care of its spread for more than 30 years.
The event is run by hundreds of volunteers, and the flame is also a symbol of selflessness and human solidarity.
All the latest news, including a list of places where people can come to get a flame, can be found on the website www.betlemskesvetlo.cz.
