From a legal point of view, Covid is on the list of infectious diseases.
That is, in the same group as HIV, the plague, yellow fever or typhus.
§ 152 Spreading a Contagious Human Disease
(1) Whoever intentionally causes or increases the risk of the introduction or spread of a communicable disease in humans shall be punished by imprisonment for six months to three years, by a ban on activities, or by the forfeiture of property.
(2) The perpetrator will be punished by imprisonment for two to eight years,
c) breaches an important duty arising from his employment, profession, position or function or imposed on him by law, or
d) causes serious injury to health.
(3) The perpetrator will be punished by imprisonment for three to ten years if he causes serious bodily harm to at least two persons or death as a result of the act referred to in paragraph 1.
(4) The perpetrator will be punished by imprisonment for five to twelve years if he causes the death of at least two persons by the act referred to in paragraph 1.
