MMA experienced a great gala evening full of interesting results.
Things happened at UFC 269.
The outsider Julianna Peña managed to beat the legendary fighter Amanda Nunes, who had not been defeated for seven years.
Charles Oliveira did not hesitate in the lightweight division, showed a great choke against Dustin Poirier and defended the belt.
Also winning was Kai Kara-France, who quickly swept Cody Garbrandt with a technical knockout in the first round.
He also defeated his opponent, Sean O'Malley.
A surprise that no one expected.
