The American entered the mutual battle as a kind of "dwarf," since Nunes had not lost for seven years and was sharpening her teeth for another triumph.
The start of the duel was also in line with the paper predictions.
Nunes started the fight very actively and even gave her opponent a push kick, which sent her to the ground.
However, Peňová did not allow herself to make any more mistakes and she herself unsuccessfully tried to attack with an armlock.
The second round was gripping and very tense for MMA fans.
Both rivals traded a series of excellent punches and hard hooks.
Peña then threw Nunes to the ground, where she began to choke her.
She had to give up the effort and fend off the attack.
The American woman thus prepared a huge shock for everyone when she became the new champion.
