New timetables come into force in Prague on Sunday, mainly affecting suburban services
Passengers in Prague's integrated transport system (PID) can expect several changes from Sunday, which will mainly affect suburban services.
New lines have been created, some have changed their routes, and others have disappeared.
The Mladá Boleslav region is now joining the integrated system.
From Sunday, express trains from České Budějovice will stop at the Zahradní Město station in the capital.
The S7 suburban trains will run on the route from Beroun to Český Brod, passing through the Prague main station.
The recently opened station in Prague-Zahradní Město will now be served by the R17 express train from České Budějovice and Benešov.
The PID will now be extended to other areas.
Buses will also go as far as Světlá nad Sázavou, Blatná near Jesenice, Staré Splavy and Turnov.
Buses in the Mladá Boleslav region will be included, including lines with connections to the Liberec and Hradec Králové regions.
During the integration, 77 lines will be cancelled, 37 new lines will be introduced and the operation of 12 existing lines will be adjusted.
A new bus line 405 will depart from Prague's Zličín, which will go all the way to Žatec.
A new direct connection between Prague and Kralovice near Rakovník has also been established, replacing the discontinued S53 train line.
The morning peak and weekend services from Prague to Rakovník will be strengthened, with the new express line number 404.
The PID system now includes lines 400 and 410 running to the Liberec region.
They depart from the Střížkov metro station, not from the Holešovice train station.
The 400 spine line runs through Mělník, Dubá and Česká Lípa to Nový Bor, and selected services continue to Rumburk or Cvikov.
The additional line 410 runs through Mělník and Dubá to Doksy, Mimoň and Jablonné v Podještědí.
On the other hand, the operation of dozens of local lines in the Central Bohemian region has been cancelled or restricted, including lines to Mochov, Dobříš and Rožmitál pod Třemšínem.
All trains departing from Prague at 02:30 have been cancelled.
Due to the modernisation of the railway, long-term restrictions continue on the Prague – Beroun, Prague – Lysá nad Labem and in the vicinity of Kolín lines.
Changes are also coming for passengers at other locations.
Buses are replacing some of the cancelled train lines or the section of line 420 from Dobříš with connections from Prague, where it is possible to use PID tickets all the way to Milevsko.
The routes of lines 540 to 543 in Nymburk have been changed, and the routes of some buses on the border of Central Bohemia and Hořovice in the Pilsen Region have been adjusted.
