In Ústí nad Labem, a hole in the road in the form of a channel without a cover lay there for a month.
It was a matter of life and death.
The city council referred the complaints to the Road and Motorway Directorate, which owns the road, and since it allegedly did not respond, the hole continued to grow.
In the end, the authorities clarified the responsibilities and ownership, and after a month, the Road and Motorway Directorate (ŘSD) began to "intensively deal with the situation".
